quotas.name: Punjab Govt Quota
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Punjab Govt Quota**

1. Should have passed XI and XII from Punjab (or)
2. Born in Punjab (or)
3. Permanent Resident of Punjab which is any one the below

    1. Candidates who have studied for 5 years in Punjab (any 5 years) or
    2. Candidates who have studied the last 2 years just preceding XII or
    3. Children or Wards of

       1. Employees of Punjab Govt working for 3 years in service (posting can be even outside Punjab state) (or)
       2. Employees of Govt of India posted in Chandigarh or Punjab for a period of 3 years
       3. Employees of State Govt institutions/undertakings posted in CG or Punjab for 3 years
       4. 3 years employed in Autonomous bodies / Companies in which Punjab Govt that has more 20% shares
       5. Residents residing outside Punjab with GoI or Punjab Govt and their service records mention permanent address as Punjab
       6. Punjab and Haryana High Court employees in connection with Punjab state affairs with 3 years exp and have not claimed residence in CG, Haryana or any other state

   4. Children/wards of pensioners of Punjab state irrespective of whether their original state is something else or whether they are now staying outside Punjab
   5. Children / Wards of persons who settled in Punjab or had resided in Punjab for at least 5 years anytime before the application submission for profession or job

In addition the following categories too

1. Wards of Defence Personnel posted in Punjab
2. Candidates seeking admission under NRI category
3. Minority Community Candidates
4. Children/ wards of regular Central Govt / Board/ Corporations or Statutory Bodies of Central Govt - posted for min 2 years inside Punjab AND were posted even for a short duration during these 3 years  during X to XII outside of Punjab. If the person was continuously posted for last 3 years in Punjab, this relaxation is not applicable

---

quotas.tooltip_content:

Priority 1: NRI/Children of NRI who originally belong to the state of Punjab    
Priority 2: NRI/Children of NRI who belong to other states
OCI and PIO shall be considered for NRI Seats

quotas.name: Punjab Minority Quota
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Punjab Minority Quota**  

<u>**2A**</u>   
CMC Ludhiana - A - Punjab   
<u>**2A_To_2G_NRI**</u>    
NRI Unfilled seat converted to Common merit list 2A_to_2G (See prospectus Cat 5 NRI to Cat 2 List) 
<u>**2B**</u>    
CMC Ludhiana - B - Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Kerala, Puducherry, Tamil Nadu, Telengana 
<u>**2C**</u>     
CMC Ludhiana - C - Goa, Maharashtra, Gujarat, Daman & Diu, Dadra & Nagar Haveli, Rajasthan, Lakshadweep  
<u>**2D**</u>     
CMC Ludhiana - D - Madhya Pradesh, Chhatisgarh, Orissa, Jharkhand, West Bengal, Andaman & Nicobar, Islands    
<u>**2E**</u>     
CMC Ludhiana - E - Uttar Pradesh, Bihar, Uttarakhand, Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, CMC Ludhiana - Meghalaya, Manipur, Mizoram, Nagaland, Sikkim, Tripura   
<u>**2F**</u>  
CMC Ludhiana - F - Jammu & Kashmir, Ladakh, Himachal Pradesh, Delhi, Haryana, Chandigarh
<u>**2G**</u>     
CMC Ludhiana - G - Service Commitment with CMC Ludhiana & Its Outreach Centers. Candidates applying in the 2G category should have their forms endorsed by the Director, Christian Medical College Ludhiana. (Sponsored by CMC Ludhiana itself through a process of application)     
<u>**OPEN**</u>    
Sikh Minority All India Basis - To Be verified

quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Punjab Management Quota**

<u>**Backward Area, BC, Border Area, Defence, FF, Handi, JK, PP, RA, SC, Sports, TA**</u>    
1. Should have passed XI and XII from Punjab (or)
2. Born in Punjab (or)
3.  Permanent Resident of Punjab which is any one the below

    1. Candidates who have studied for 5 years in Punjab (any 5 years) or
    2. Candidates who have studied the last 2 years just preceding XII or
    3. Children or Wards of

        1. Employees of Punjab Govt working for 3 years in service (posting can be even outside Punjab state) (or)
        2. Employees of Govt of India posted in Chandigarh or Punjab for a period of 3 years
       3. Employees of State Govt institutions/undertakings posted in CG or Punjab for 3 years
       4. 3 years employed in Autonomous bodies / Companies in which Punjab Govt that has more 20% shares
       5. Residents residing outside Punjab with GoI or Punjab Govt and their service records mention permanent address as Punjab
       6. Punjab and Haryana High Court employees in connection with Punjab state affairs with 3 years exp and have not claimed residence in CG, Haryana or any other state

    4. Children/wards of pensioners of Punjab state irrespective of whether their original state is something else or whether they are now staying outside Punjab
    5. Children / Wards of persons who settled in Punjab or had resided in Punjab for at least 5 years anytime before the application submission for profession or job

In addition the following categories too

1. Wards of Defence Personnel posted in Punjab
2. Candidates seeking admission under NRI category
3. Minority Community Candidates
4. Children/ wards of regular Central Govt / Board/ Corporations or Statutory Bodies of Central Govt - posted for min 2 years inside Punjab AND were posted even for a short duration during these 3 years  during X to XII outside of Punjab. If the person was continuously posted for last 3 years in Punjab, this relaxation is not applicable

<u>**OPEN**</u>  

All India Basis-To be verified

<u>**Backward Area, BC, Border Area, Defence, FF, Handi, JK, PP, RA, SC, Sports, TA**</u>    
1. Should have passed XI and XII from Punjab (or)
2. Born in Punjab (or)
3.  Permanent Resident of Punjab which is any one the below

    1. Candidates who have studied for 5 years in Punjab (any 5 years) or
    2. Candidates who have studied the last 2 years just preceding XII or
    3. Children or Wards of

        1. Employees of Punjab Govt working for 3 years in service (posting can be even outside Punjab state) (or)
        2. Employees of Govt of India posted in Chandigarh or Punjab for a period of 3 years
       3. Employees of State Govt institutions/undertakings posted in CG or Punjab for 3 years
       4. 3 years employed in Autonomous bodies / Companies in which Punjab Govt that has more 20% shares
       5. Residents residing outside Punjab with GoI or Punjab Govt and their service records mention permanent address as Punjab
       6. Punjab and Haryana High Court employees in connection with Punjab state affairs with 3 years exp and have not claimed residence in CG, Haryana or any other state

    4. Children/wards of pensioners of Punjab state irrespective of whether their original state is something else or whether they are now staying outside Punjab
    5. Children / Wards of persons who settled in Punjab or had resided in Punjab for at least 5 years anytime before the application submission for profession or job

In addition the following categories too

1. Wards of Defence Personnel posted in Punjab
2. Candidates seeking admission under NRI category
3. Minority Community Candidates
4. Children/ wards of regular Central Govt / Board/ Corporations or Statutory Bodies of Central Govt - posted for min 2 years inside Punjab AND were posted even for a short duration during these 3 years  during X to XII outside of Punjab. If the person was continuously posted for last 3 years in Punjab, this relaxation is not applicable

<u>**OPEN**</u>  

All India Basis-To be verified

quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Punjab Management Quota**

<u>**Backward Area, BC, Border Area, Defence, FF, Handi, JK, PP, RA, SC, Sports, TA**</u>    
1. Should have passed XI and XII from Punjab (or)
2. Born in Punjab (or)
3.  Permanent Resident of Punjab which is any one the below

    1. Candidates who have studied for 5 years in Punjab (any 5 years) or
    2. Candidates who have studied the last 2 years just preceding XII or
    3. Children or Wards of

        1. Employees of Punjab Govt working for 3 years in service (posting can be even outside Punjab state) (or)
        2. Employees of Govt of India posted in Chandigarh or Punjab for a period of 3 years
       3. Employees of State Govt institutions/undertakings posted in CG or Punjab for 3 years
       4. 3 years employed in Autonomous bodies / Companies in which Punjab Govt that has more 20% shares
       5. Residents residing outside Punjab with GoI or Punjab Govt and their service records mention permanent address as Punjab
       6. Punjab and Haryana High Court employees in connection with Punjab state affairs with 3 years exp and have not claimed residence in CG, Haryana or any other state

    4. Children/wards of pensioners of Punjab state irrespective of whether their original state is something else or whether they are now staying outside Punjab
    5. Children / Wards of persons who settled in Punjab or had resided in Punjab for at least 5 years anytime before the application submission for profession or job

In addition the following categories too

1. Wards of Defence Personnel posted in Punjab
2. Candidates seeking admission under NRI category
3. Minority Community Candidates
4. Children/ wards of regular Central Govt / Board/ Corporations or Statutory Bodies of Central Govt - posted for min 2 years inside Punjab AND were posted even for a short duration during these 3 years  during X to XII outside of Punjab. If the person was continuously posted for last 3 years in Punjab, this relaxation is not applicable

<u>**OPEN**</u>  

All India Basis-To be verified

<u>**Backward Area, BC, Border Area, Defence, FF, Handi, JK, PP, RA, SC, Sports, TA**</u>    
1. Should have passed XI and XII from Punjab (or)
2. Born in Punjab (or)
3.  Permanent Resident of Punjab which is any one the below

    1. Candidates who have studied for 5 years in Punjab (any 5 years) or
    2. Candidates who have studied the last 2 years just preceding XII or
    3. Children or Wards of

        1. Employees of Punjab Govt working for 3 years in service (posting can be even outside Punjab state) (or)
        2. Employees of Govt of India posted in Chandigarh or Punjab for a period of 3 years
       3. Employees of State Govt institutions/undertakings posted in CG or Punjab for 3 years
       4. 3 years employed in Autonomous bodies / Companies in which Punjab Govt that has more 20% shares
       5. Residents residing outside Punjab with GoI or Punjab Govt and their service records mention permanent address as Punjab
       6. Punjab and Haryana High Court employees in connection with Punjab state affairs with 3 years exp and have not claimed residence in CG, Haryana or any other state

    4. Children/wards of pensioners of Punjab state irrespective of whether their original state is something else or whether they are now staying outside Punjab
    5. Children / Wards of persons who settled in Punjab or had resided in Punjab for at least 5 years anytime before the application submission for profession or job

In addition the following categories too

1. Wards of Defence Personnel posted in Punjab
2. Candidates seeking admission under NRI category
3. Minority Community Candidates
4. Children/ wards of regular Central Govt / Board/ Corporations or Statutory Bodies of Central Govt - posted for min 2 years inside Punjab AND were posted even for a short duration during these 3 years  during X to XII outside of Punjab. If the person was continuously posted for last 3 years in Punjab, this relaxation is not applicable

<u>**OPEN**</u>  

All India Basis-To be verified

**Eligibility for the Quota : Punjab Govt Quota**

1. Should have passed XI and XII from Punjab (or)
2. Born in Punjab (or)
3. Permanent Resident of Punjab which is any one the below

    1. Candidates who have studied for 5 years in Punjab (any 5 years) or
    2. Candidates who have studied the last 2 years just preceding XII or
    3. Children or Wards of

       1. Employees of Punjab Govt working for 3 years in service (posting can be even outside Punjab state) (or)
       2. Employees of Govt of India posted in Chandigarh or Punjab for a period of 3 years
       3. Employees of State Govt institutions/undertakings posted in CG or Punjab for 3 years
       4. 3 years employed in Autonomous bodies / Companies in which Punjab Govt that has more 20% shares
       5. Residents residing outside Punjab with GoI or Punjab Govt and their service records mention permanent address as Punjab
       6. Punjab and Haryana High Court employees in connection with Punjab state affairs with 3 years exp and have not claimed residence in CG, Haryana or any other state

   4. Children/wards of pensioners of Punjab state irrespective of whether their original state is something else or whether they are now staying outside Punjab
   5. Children / Wards of persons who settled in Punjab or had resided in Punjab for at least 5 years anytime before the application submission for profession or job

In addition the following categories too

1. Wards of Defence Personnel posted in Punjab
2. Candidates seeking admission under NRI category
3. Minority Community Candidates
4. Children/ wards of regular Central Govt / Board/ Corporations or Statutory Bodies of Central Govt - posted for min 2 years inside Punjab AND were posted even for a short duration during these 3 years  during X to XII outside of Punjab. If the person was continuously posted for last 3 years in Punjab, this relaxation is not applicable

---

quota.name: Punjab Open Quota
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Punjab Open Quota**  

<u>**Backward Area, BC, Border Area, Defence, FF, Handi, JK, OPEN, PP, RA, SC, Sports, TA**</u>

1. Should have passed XI and XII from Punjab (or)
2.  Born in Punjab (or)
3. Permanent Resident of Punjab which is any one the below

   1. Candidates who have studied for 5 years in Punjab (any 5 years) or
   2. Candidates who have studied the last 2 years just preceeding XII or
   3. Children or Wards of

      1. Employees of Punjab Govt working for 3 years in service (posting can be even outisde Punjab state) (or)
      2. Employees of Govt of India posted in Chandigarh or Punjab for a period of 3 years
      3. Employees of State Govt institutions/undertakings posted in CG or Punjab for 3 years
      4. 3 years employed in Autonomous bodies / Companies in which Punjab Govt that has more 20% shares
      5. Residents residing outside Punjab with GoI or Punjab Govt and their service records mention permanent address as Punjab
      6. Punjab and Haryana High Court employees in connection with Punjab state affairs with 3 years exp and have not claimed residence in CG, Haryana or any other state

    4. Children/wards of pensioners of Punjab state irrespective of whether their original state is something else or whether they are now staying outside Punjab
    5. Children / Wards of persons who settled in Punjab or had resided in Punjab for at leasrt 5 years anytime before the application submission for profession or job

In addition the following categories too

1. Wards of Defence Personnel posted in Punjab
2. Candidates seeking admission under NRI category
3. Minority Community Candidates
4. Children/ wards of regular Central Govt / Board/ Corporations or Statutory Bodies of Central Govt - posted for min 2 years inside Punjab AND were posted even for a short duration during these 3 years  during X to XII outside of Punjab. If the person was continuously posted for last 3 years in Punjab, this relaxation is not applicable


<u>**AIQ**</u>  

All India Basis

quota.name: Punjab Govt Quota
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Punjab Govt Quota**

1. Should have passed XI and XII from Punjab (or)
2. Born in Punjab (or)
3. Permanent Resident of Punjab which is any one the below

    1. Candidates who have studied for 5 years in Punjab (any 5 years) or
    2. Candidates who have studied the last 2 years just preceding XII or
    3. Children or Wards of

       1. Employees of Punjab Govt working for 3 years in service (posting can be even outside Punjab state) (or)
       2. Employees of Govt of India posted in Chandigarh or Punjab for a period of 3 years
       3. Employees of State Govt institutions/undertakings posted in CG or Punjab for 3 years
       4. 3 years employed in Autonomous bodies / Companies in which Punjab Govt that has more 20% shares
       5. Residents residing outside Punjab with GoI or Punjab Govt and their service records mention permanent address as Punjab
       6. Punjab and Haryana High Court employees in connection with Punjab state affairs with 3 years exp and have not claimed residence in CG, Haryana or any other state

   4. Children/wards of pensioners of Punjab state irrespective of whether their original state is something else or whether they are now staying outside Punjab
   5. Children / Wards of persons who settled in Punjab or had resided in Punjab for at least 5 years anytime before the application submission for profession or job

In addition the following categories too

1. Wards of Defence Personnel posted in Punjab
2. Candidates seeking admission under NRI category
3. Minority Community Candidates
4. Children/ wards of regular Central Govt / Board/ Corporations or Statutory Bodies of Central Govt - posted for min 2 years inside Punjab AND were posted even for a short duration during these 3 years  during X to XII outside of Punjab. If the person was continuously posted for last 3 years in Punjab, this relaxation is not applicable

   5. Children / Wards of persons who settled in Punjab or had resided in Punjab for at least 5 years anytime before the application submission for profession or job
